  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis in an OpenType variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` provides the metadata for one variation axis of an
OpenType variable font: its four-byte tag, minimum/default/maximum design
values, and whether it should be hidden from UI.

Retrieve axis infos via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters>
or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters(System.Span{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis})>.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("Roboto-VF.ttf");
foreach (var axis in typeface.VariationDesignParameters)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"{axis.Tag}: min={axis.Min} def={axis.Default} max={axis.Max}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
